 for bestpractices and # Company Detail & IPI

## Overview
Create a focused, auditable UI suite for Investor Perception Index (IPI) around a selected company and time window. The pages provide an end-to-end, explainable view of how narratives, credibility signals, and risk contribute to the IPI, with drill-down capabilities to underlying NarrativeEvents and raw payloads. The system must be resilient, null-safe, and strictly guard against null/undefined values before using array methods or rendering data. The implementation must follow the runtime safety rules outlined in the project context and integrate with the Gbox360 narrative model (even if the current data sources are mockups for MVP). The experience should be design-system driven, accessible, and responsive, with audit-friendly raw payload access and export capabilities.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Company Detail & IPI page presents a focused view for a selected company and a chosen time window. It surfaces a complete IPI breakdown (Narrative, Credibility, Risk), a full narrative list with provenance, a timeline of narrative movement (time-decayed persistence), and an auditable Raw Payload viewer for each event. Users can see the current IPI score, directional change, and a comparison to prior windows/historical baselines.

Goals:
- Deliver a single-source-of-truth view for a company/time window with actionable explanations for IPI movements.
- Provide direct, contextual drill-down paths to NarrativeEvents and their raw payloads.
- Enable efficient search and filter across companies, narratives, and events by time window, source, and speaker role.
- Support an audit artifact workflow (exportable payloads and summaries).

Connected features:
- IPI Explainability & Drill-down UI: Explanations of IPI movements with links to NarrativeEvents and raw payloads.
- Search & Filter: Global search for companies, narratives, events; filter by time window, source, and speaker role.
- Narrative Drill-down: Deep dive page explaining why a narrative contributed to an IPI movement, linking to underlying NarrativeEvents and raw payloads.
- Dashboard: Primary workspace post-login showing IPI summary for the selected company and window, directional trend, top narratives, quick search, and recent activity.

UI elements and how they should look and behave:
- Company header: logo, company name, ticker, sector, short description.
- IPI Breakdown panel: a visualization (preferably a stacked bar or donut) showing Narrative, Credibility, and Risk contributions with precise numeric values.
- Timeline: an interactive time-series or time-decayed narrative persistence timeline with zoom/pan, range selectors, and annotation points for events.
- Narrative list: expandable items showing narrative title, contributing events, authority weighting, credibility proxy score, and a toggle to view the raw payloads.
- Raw Payload viewer: modal or panel showing preserved payload JSON/text with source metadata, and options to download.
- Time window picker: allow selecting a window; provide a comparison view against prior windows and history baseline.
- Export artifacts: CTA to export an audit artifact (e.g., JSON/CSV) including IPI breakdown, contributing narratives, and raw payload links.

Visual guidance:
- The design system emphasizes warmth, clarity, and audit readiness. Use pastel-tinted tiles for narrative summaries, consistent rounded cards, and accessible typography. Ensure high-contrast text, adequate focus outlines, and responsive behavior.

## Components to Build
- CompanyDetailIPIHeader
  - Props: companyId, companyName, ticker, sector, description, logoUrl
  - Behavior: fetch or receive company context; render header with responsive layout.

- IPI BreakdownPanel
  - Props: narrativePct, credibilityPct, riskPct, totals
  - Behavior: render a stacked/segmented visual with numeric values; accessible labels for screen readers; tooltip on hover with exact numbers.

- NarrativeTimeline
  - Props: events[], windowRange
  - Behavior: render interactive timeline; support zoom, pan, and range selection; show decay-weighted contributions.

- NarrativeList
  - Props: narratives[], onExpand, onOpenRawPayload
  - Behavior: render collapsible items; each item shows title, weight, credibility proxy, and a link to raw payload.

- NarrativeEventCard (used inside NarrativeList)
  - Props: narrative, events[]
  - Behavior: show contributing events with a summary; show "View Details" to drill down.

- RawPayloadModal
  - Props: payload, meta
  - Behavior: show JSON payload with syntax highlighting (optional), metadata, and "Download" button.

- TimeWindowPicker
  - Props: currentWindow, onChange
  - Behavior: select start/end dates; quick presets (Last 7d, 30d, YTD); comparison toggle to prior window.

- ComparePanel
  - Props: currentWindowStats, previousWindowStats, baselineStats
  - Behavior: display side-by-side IPI metrics and deltas.

- SearchFilterBar
  - Props: query, filters, onQueryChange, onFiltersChange
  - Behavior: global search; filters for time window, source, speaker role; debounced input.

- AuditExportButton
  - Props: payloadData
  - Behavior: generate artifact with IPI breakdown, narratives, events, and download option.

- DashboardSummaryCard
  - Props: companyId, window, currentIpi, delta, topNarratives
  - Behavior: high-level overview for quick access from Dashboard.

- NarrativeDrilldownPage (separate route/page)
  - Props: narrativeId
  - Behavior: deep dive explanation of a narrative’s contribution, with links to NarrativeEvents and raw payloads.

- PageLayout
  - Global layout: header, navigation, content container, responsive grid.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Ensure all arrays are initialized to empty arrays with proper type defaults:
  - useState<MyType[]>([]) for arrays
- Guard all data accesses against null/undefined:
  - Use (data ?? []) when mapping over results
  - Array.isArray checks for any dynamic data
  - Optional chaining for nested API responses
  - Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}
- Components must fetch data via a centralized data layer with:
  - Endpoints to fetch: company context, IPI breakdown, narratives, events, raw payloads
  - Use a consistent data shape, with safe fallbacks
- Implement robust error handling and loading states; display accessible empty states if no data
- Accessibility: aria-labels, keyboard navigation, proper color contrast, focus outlines
- Performance: paginate narrative lists, lazy-load timeline items, avoid unnecessary re-renders
- State management: use React context or a lightweight global store for the selected company and window, with proper resets on route changes
- Testing: unit tests for safe guards (null/undefined), integration tests for data fetch flows, and end-to-end checks for key user journeys
- API integration hooks should adhere to the provided runtime safety rules:
  - const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - const items = data ?? []
- Data visualization should lean on accessible components; if charts are used, ensure they have accessible labels and fallbacks

### Backend
- APIs to implement (or stub for MVP):
  - GET /api/companies/{companyId}/ipi?start={}&end={}
    - Returns: { currentIpi, delta, breakdown: { narrative, credibility, risk }, narratives: Narrative[], events: NarrativeEvent[], window }
  - GET /api/companies/{companyId}/ipi/narratives?start=&end=&search=&filters[]
    - Returns: Narrative[] with fields: id, title, weight, credibilityProxy, contributingEventIds[]
  - GET /api/narratives/{narrativeId}/events
    - Returns: NarrativeEvent[] with fields: id, source, speaker, role, rawPayload, timestamp
  - GET /api/events/{eventId}/payload
    - Returns: { payloadJson, metadata }
  - POST /api/audit/export
    - Body: { companyId, windowStart, windowEnd, data: { breakdown, narratives, events } }
    - Returns: downloadable artifact (JSON/CSV)
- Data models (schema-level)
